<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0959B207ECC5F89822924D8F" blockId="13.[151,1436,1608,2031]" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0959B207ECC5F89821A84D77" bold="true" box="[199,419,1860,1886]" pageId="13" pageNumber="464">Short description:</emphasis>
It is distinguished by having 15–18 gill rakers on lower limb of first gill arch, a pale or deeply orange spot at upper opercle, a bold black middle caudal-fin rays with white membrane, a white dorsal-fin tip, and orange anal, pectoral and ventral fins.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
